AB  - The iconic conifer Araucaria araucana (Araucaria), called Pehuén by native people, is an endemic species of the Andes of northern Patagonia in Chile and Argentina. Its range encompasses only three degrees of latitude (37 ◦ 20 – 40 ◦ 20 S) with a small outlying presence in the coastal mountains of Chile (Veblen et al. 1995). The species is classified as endangered (Premoli et al. 2013) because of extensive logging and human-set fires. 
